burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames

Class JointAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames.JointAction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractGroundedAction, java.lang.Iterable<GroundedSGAgentAction>

    public class JointAction
extends java.lang.Object
implements AbstractGroundedAction, java.lang.Iterable<GroundedSGAgentAction>
    This class specifies which action each agent took in a world. The class is backed by a Map from agent names to the GroundedSGAgentAction taken by that respective agent. The GroundedSGAgentAction objects of this class can also be iterated over.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan

This method can be useful for generating hash codes since two grounded single actions with different parameter orders may be the same action if the parameters belong to the same order group.
